{"quote": "An American commando", "page_title": "Tom Clancy's Splinter Cell", "page_bio": "Tom Clancys Splinter Cell (2002) is the first game in the Splinter Cell series of books and video games. Released in late 2002, the game follows National Security Agency agent and former United States Navy SEALs officer Sam Fisher (Splinter Cell), a \"Splinter Cell\" in the counter-terrorist group \"Third Echelon\", a division of the NSA, as he investigates the mysterious disappearance of two Central Intelligence Agency intelligence officers in Tbilisi, which leads him to uncover a plot involving mass conspiracy and high-tech information warfare.", "page_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom Clancy's Splinter Cell"}